    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.85/10–1747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 17, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>711. Embassy today received Foreign Office reply dated October 15<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d517fn1">Not printed; it was transmitted to the Department by the
                        Ambassador in his despatch 49, October 21, 1947.</note> to Embassy note 596
                        [<hi rend="italic">598</hi>] of August 27 Embassy despatch No. 31 October
                        10<note n="12" xml:id="d517fn2">Not printed.</note> concerning
                    discriminations against American shipping. With reference to Law 10 of 1946,
                    Foreign Office points out foreign companies have access to Colombian courts and
                    Council of State. With reference to discrimination by Coffee Federation, Foreign
                    Office maintains latter is private entity. It also reminds Embassy that by
                    virtue of Public Resolution 17 passed by 73rd Congress<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d517fn3">48 Stat. 500.</note> exportation of American products
                    obtained through loans made by official entities must be exported exclusively in
                    ships of American registry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
